 phenomenon and those wanting a new light on Chinese culture and society will find it equally useful. To those with a particular interest in Chinese theater, it will be a rich and important resource.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aChinese dramaxHistory and criticism. 0aTheaterzChina. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Theater / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aDolby, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHu, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMackerras, Colin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMackerras, Colin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aScott, A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWichmann, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHawaii eBook Package Archive pre 2000z978311056415040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824842499423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780824842499.jpg  a978-3-11-056415-0  Hawaii eBook Package Archive pre 2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK